Fixes ScatterSkyVertex size. 

Not a problem in DX9 because currently, the vertex attribute is not used. But in OpenGL, the size of the vertices is checked and produces a AssertFatal.

```
GFXDeclareVertexFormat( ScatterSkyVertex )
{
   Point3F point;
   VectorF normal;
   ColorF color; // size of 16 bytes, need to change to GFXVertexColor (size of 4 bytes)
};

GFXImplementVertexFormat( ScatterSkyVertex )
{
   addElement( "POSITION", GFXDeclType_Float3 );
   addElement( "NORMAL", GFXDeclType_Float3 );
   addElement( "COLOR", GFXDeclType_Color ); // size of 4 bytes
}
```

How reproduce it:
- On `engine/source/platform/test/test/ThreadPool.cpp` change:

```
void run()
   {
      U32 numItems = Con::getIntVariable( "$testThreadPool::numValues", DEFAULT_NUM_ITEMS );
#if 1 // change this line
      ThreadPool* pool = &ThreadPool::GLOBAL(); // TODO use global thread pool cause crash on app exit.
#else
      ThreadPool localThreadPool("localThreadPool");
      ThreadPool* pool = &localThreadPool;
#endif
      results.setSize( numItems );

      for( U32 i = 0; i < numItems; ++ i )
         results[ i ] = U32( -1 );
```
- Compile
- Run T3D
- In the main menu
- Open the console
- unitTest_runTests ("", true)
- Wait until all test run
- Click the Exit button
